The government has started reforms to clean up and improve the quality of university education.The emphasis will shift from creating institutions to improving existing ones.Education PS Collete Suda said on Thursday they are weeding out undeserving staff and students.She said the reforms will mean varsities will only have qualified students and staff. &ldquo;Universities must admit only those students who meet the requirement for the programmes they are specialising on. Those programmes should in turn be delivered by qualified and competent staff, who are hired competitively on merit,&rdquo; the PS said.Suda spoke during the South Eastern Kenya University graduation ceremony at Kwa Vonza campus in Kitui.She said with 31 public and 40 private universities, the country has achieved a lot in promoting access to university education.